                           <p  style="font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;">  Being thus instructed by Narad, Prahlad maharaj, when sent to school by his father, started preaching to his friends about bhakti and transformed all the demoniac children in to devotees. He gave them the instruction of nava vidha bhakti, which are the nine prominent kinds of bhakti out of the sixty four angas of bhakti mentioned in the shastras.</p><br> 

                           <p style="font-size: 16px">                        
							sri-prahlada uvaca<br>
							sravanam kirtanam visnoh<br>
							smaranam pada-sevanam<br> 
							arcanam vandanam dasyam<br>
							sakhyam atma-nivedanam<br><br>

							iti pumsarpita visnau<br>
							bhaktis cen nava-laksana<br>
							kriyeta bhagavaty addha<br>
							tan manye ‘dhitam uttamam<br>
							(Srimad-Bhagavatam, 7.5.23-24)</p> <br><br>


